<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Crimes reported to law enforcement agencies
nationwide increased 1 percent during the first six months of 1988
over the same period last year.
   Figures released by FBI's Uniform Crime Reporting Office on
Saturday showed reported violent crimes of murder, forcible rape,
robbery and aggravated assault increased 5 percent as a group.
   At the same time, the reported property crimes of burglary,
larceny, theft and motor vehicle theft increased 1 percent.
   Regionally, the Northeast showed the largest increase in violent
crime, 7 percent over the first six months of last year.
