<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0406</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rain Covers Much of East; Temperatures Near Freezing in Great
Lakes</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain fell over much of the East from New England to Florida and
the Gulf Coast early today while northerly winds chilled
temperatures in the upper Great Lakes region.
   Early morning showers stretched from eastern New England to
eastern Virginia and northern North Carolina. Rain also fell on the
southern Appalachians, northern Alabama and northern Mississippi.
   Showers and thunderstorms hit southern Alabama, Mississippi and
Georgia and northern Florida. McComb, Miss., recorded 1.95 inches
of rain in the six hours ended at 2 a.m. EDT, but rainfall
elsewhere was moderate.
   Scattered rain also fell on upper Michigan and northwest New
York state, but skies were generally fair over the rest of the
nation.
   Northerly winds dropped temperatures into the low to mid 30s in
upper Michigan and northern Minnesota.
   Today's forecast called for rain along the East Coast from
southern New England to the Carolinas and southern Georgia and
northern Florida. Rain also was forecast for upper Michigan and
northeast Minnesota and strong, gusty winds were expected in North
Dakota.
   Highs were predicted to be in the 40s and 50s in the northern
Plains, the upper Mississippi Valley, the Great Lakes and northern
New England; in the 80s from South Carolina across Florida, much of
Texas, and from the central and southern Rockies across to southern
Oregon; and in the 90s to near 105 degrees in the desert Southwest.
Highs elsewhere were expected to be in the 60s and 70s.
   At 3 a.m. EDT, temperatures ranged from 30 degrees at Marquette,
Mich., to 85 at Yuma, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 68 rain; Boston 65 partly cloudy; Buffalo 48
fair; Charleston, S.C. 71 foggy; Cincinnati 50 fair; Cleveland 50
partly cloudy; Detroit 48 fair; Miami 79 fair; New York 66 partly
cloudy; Philadelphia 64 foggy; Pittsburgh 55 cloudy; Portland,
Maine 63 fair; Washington 65 foggy.
   _Central: Bismarck 51 cloudy; Chicago 49 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
57 fair; Denver 48 fair; Des Moines 41 fair; Indianapolis 44 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 39 fair; Nashville 62 partly cloudy; New
Orleans 66 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 58 fair; Anchorage 52 cloudy; Las Vegas 73
fair; Los Angeles 61 foggy; Phoenix 81 fair; Salt Lake City 52
fair; San Diego 65 foggy; San Francisco 60 cloudy; Seattle 52 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 43 partly cloudy.
