Lebanon. It as not clear whether anyone was hurt in the explosion.
   The 2,000-man militia patrols the 6-to-10-mile deep security
zone jointly with Israeli troops.
   The buffer was established after Israel withdrew the bulk of its
occupation force from south Lebanon in 1985, ending a three-year
invasion.
