<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Obit-Satterfield     10-03 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Satterfield,0203</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former Virginia Congressman Dies at Age 67</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Rep. David E. Satterfield III, a
conservative Democrat who represented Virginia's 3rd District in
Congress for 16 years, has died at age 67.
   Satterfield died Friday of heart failure at the Medical College
of Virginia Hospital, said college spokeswoman Stephanie Halloran.
   He was first elected to the House in 1964 from the Richmond area
district and retired in 1980. Before entering Congress, he served
on the Richmond City Council from 1954 to 1956 and in the Virginia
House of Delegates from 1960 to 1964.
   In Congress, Satterfield was known as a stauch defender of
tobacco interests. His support of conservative causes hurt him with
his more liberal Democratic colleagues in the House and cost him a
subcommittee chairmanship in 1979.
   When he retired, Satterfield supported a Republican to succeed
him, Rep. Thomas J. Bliley.
   ``He was a good friend, and he was very helpful to me when I was
first elected,'' Bliley said. ``He has helped me in every election
since.''
   Satterfield is survived by his wife, two sons and a brother. A
memorial service was scheduled for today in Richmond.
</TEXT>
