<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Jonas,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former U.S. Rep. Charlie Jonas Dead at 85</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LINCOLNTON, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former U.S. Rep. Charlie Jonas, who was
known as ``Mr. Republican'' in North Carolina during his 20 years
in Congress, has died at 85.
   Some 250 people, including Republican Gov. Jim Martin, attended
a funeral service Saturday in Jonas' hometown of Lincolnton.
   Jonas, who died Wednesday, was first elected to Congress in
1952. He was re-elected nine times on a pledge of fiscal
conservatism.
   His father, Charles A. Jonas, was the state's first Republican
elected to Congress since the turn of the century.
   ``Charlie Jonas was a great inspiration to me in my political
career,'' said Martin, who succeeded Jonas in the 9th District
congressional seat before being elected governor. ``He was a good
counselor from time to time when as a young congressman, I needed
it.''
   Jonas is survived by a son and a sister.
</TEXT>
