<1ST_LINE>r a PM-AdrienneBrown-Drugs     10-03 0166</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Adrienne Brown-Drugs,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soul Singer's Wife Guilty Of Drug Possession</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MERRIMACK, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of soul singer James Brown has
been convicted of a drug charge and fined $330, a court official
said today.
   Adrienne Brown, 38, of Aiken, S.C., appeared in Merrimack
District Court on Friday on a charge of possession of the drug PCP
based on lab tests on the contents of a plastic container. The
container was confiscated last May when a fire broke out in a
Bedford hotel where she and her husband were staying.
   She also was charged with arson and criminal mischief following
the May 10 fire. Mrs. Brown said she wasn't in the hotel room when
the fire began.
   The Hillsborough County attorney declined to seek indictments on
the fire-related charges.
   Mrs. Brown and her husband were in New Hampshire for a concert
performance.
   Last month, in Augusta, Ga., Mrs. Brown withdrew a guilty plea
to two drug charges stemming from arrests in April and May.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
