<HEAD>British Tourists Arrive Home From Greece 56 Hours Late</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of 150 British travelers arrived home
Monday, 56 hours after they set out on what was to be a four-hour
trip from Greece.
   ``We felt like a cargo of toxic waste that nobody wanted,'' said
Sara Hind, a costume designer, when the group reached London's
Gatwick airport at 2 a.m. They left the resort island of Skiathos
in the northern Aegean Sea on Friday.
   Airport officials said passengers were delayed by a 48-hour
strike of Greek civil aviation workers. Officials said hundreds of
tourists were transferred by sea from closed island airports to the
mainland and bused to Athens airport.
   ``When we finally landed at Gatwick, we gave ourselves a round
of applause for sticking it through without going round the bend
(mad),'' Ms. Hind said.
