<HEAD>Police Say Another Mob Killing in Catania</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CATANIA, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two gunmen on a motorcycle drove up to a
car Monday and killed its driver, police said, counting the murder
as Catania's 57th Mafia-linked killing this year, the Italian news
agency ANSA reported.
   One other man in the car was wounded and taken to a hospital for
surgery, ANSA said. It quoted police as identifying him as
Francesco Sapuppo, 35, suspected of being a member of a Mafia clan
based in Catania, eastern Sicily's largest city with 375,00
inhabitants.
   ANSA said police speculated the intended target was Sapuppo.
   The dead man, shot in the chest and head by pistol fire, was
identified by police as Maurizio Bilieri, 23, ANSA said.
   Authorities say rival clans in the area are engaged in a
struggle for power.
</TEXT>
