hearing the federal government's huge fraud case against the Wall
Street firm.
   Their petition late Friday to the 2nd U.S. Circuit Court of
Appeals reflected the aggressive approach that Drexel's defense
team has taken in fighting the Securities and Exchange Commission's
sweeping allegations since they were announced Sept. 7.
