<TEXT>
   Japan's merchandise trade surplus has edged back
up, confounding expectations, economists say.
   The Finance Ministry on Friday reported the second straight
increase in the merchandise trade surplus component of the current
account following a year of declines.
   Economists continue to predict Japan's surplus will shrink in
the long run, but they said the increases in July and August
indicated the progress will be slower than many had expected.
</TEXT>
