closed with a 6.40 loss at 2,112.91.
   Crude oil prices plummeted to their lowest levels in more than
two years. On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the contract for
November delivery of West Texas Intermediate fell 55 cents to
$13.37 a barrel.
   Bond prices rose sharply in reaction to the tumble in oil. The
lower interest rates knocked down the dollar.
