<1ST_LINE>r f AM-LaptopComputer     10-03 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Laptop Computer,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toshiba Announces Laptop Computers In Fashion Show</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Toshiba Corp.'s U.S. arm introduced two portable
computers and two portable printers Monday in a combination news
conference and fashion show that featured models showing off the
equipment at a New York hotel.
   The T5200, which uses Intel Corp.'s top-of-the-line 80386
microprocessor, is not a true laptop computer because it cannot run
on batteries. It is also heavier than most laptops, at just under
19 pounds.
   The T1600, which is built on Intel's 80C286 chip, can run on
batteries and weighs in at 11.6 pounds. Toshiba called it the top
of its battery-powered PC line.
   The T5200 has a suggested retail price of $9,499 to $10,999 and
will be available later this year. The T1600 is priced at $4,999
and will be available early next year, according to Toshiba America
Inc. in Irvine, Calif.
   Toshiba said the printers both provide letter-quality output.
The ExpressWriter311 is $589 and has a November delivery date,
while the ExpressWriter301 is $489 and scheduled for shipment in
February.
</TEXT>
